AMENDMENTS TO LB1126
(Amendments to Standing Committee amendments, AM2432)
Introduced by Dorn, 30.
1 1. Insert the following new sections:
2 Sec. 95. Section 86-903, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, is
3 amended to read:
4 86-903 (1) The Department of Revenue shall determine the prepaid
5 wireless surcharge annually, effective January 1, based on the charges
6 described in subsection (2) of this section as in effect on the preceding
7 July 1. The department shall provide not less than ninety days' advance
8 notice of any change in the prepaid wireless surcharge on the
9 department's website.
10 (2) The rate of the prepaid wireless surcharge shall be the sum of
11 the following three percentages, rounded up to the nearest tenth of one
12 percent:
13 (a) The percentage obtained by dividing (i) the amount of the
14 wireless surcharge authorized under subsection (1) subdivision (1)(b) of
15 section 86-1070 by (ii) fifty;
16 (b) The percentage obtained by dividing (i) the amount of the
17 Nebraska Telecommunications Relay System Fund surcharge set by the Public
18 Service Commission pursuant to the Telecommunications Relay System Act by
19 (ii) fifty; and
20 (c) The percentage obtained by multiplying (i) the Nebraska
21 Telecommunications Universal Service Fund surcharge percentage rate set
22 by the Public Service Commission by (ii) one minus the Federal
23 Communications Commission safe harbor percentage for determining the
24 interstate portion of a fixed monthly wireless charge.
25 (3) The Department of Revenue shall provide the Public Service
26 Commission with prepaid wireless surcharge calculation and collection
-1-

